-- Polish Stocks: Azoty Tarnow, KGHM Polska Miedz, Pulawy Active
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-07-16T08:27:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/polish-stocks-azoty-tarnow-kghm-polska-miedz-pulawy-active.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  dropped less
than 0.1 percent to 2,190.00 at 10:16 a.m. in Warsaw.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the country’s only copper
miner, slid 0.4 percent to 117.5 zloty as the metal declined
after China’s premier said that the momentum for a recovery in
economic growth isn’t yet in place, increasing speculation
demand may decline in the world’s largest user.  Zaklady Azotowe Pulawy SA (ZAP)  , the nation’s second-
biggest fertilizer maker, rose 0.7 percent to 104.5 zloty,
climbing for a fifth day after Azoty Tarnow (ATT PW) announced a
public bid to buy 32 percent in the company at 110 zloty a
share. Azoty advanced 1.2 percent to 38.45 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
